2025-10-31 | Diameter of Binary Tree

Problem Statement
Given the root of a binary tree, your task is to find the diameter of the binary tree.

Constraints:
•	The tree may contain positive or negative integers.
•	The number of nodes in the tree is in the range [1, 10⁴].
•	Each node contains an integer value.

Approach / Explanation
1.	Observation
•	The diameter of a binary tree can pass through or bypass the root.
•	For each node, the longest path through it equals the sum of the heights of its left and right subtrees.
•	The maximum of these values across all nodes is the diameter.

SOLUTION:
/*
class Node {
public:
    int data;
    Node* left;
    Node* right;

    Node(int val) {
        data = val;
        left = NULL;
        right = NULL;
    }
};
*/

int trav(Node* root, int &ans) {
    if (root == NULL)
        return 0;
    
    int a = trav(root->left, ans);
    int b = trav(root->right, ans);
    
    ans = max(ans, a + b + 1);
    return max(a + 1, b + 1);
}

class Solution {
  public:
    int diameter(Node* root) {
        int ans = 0;
        trav(root, ans);
        return ans - 1; // edges = nodes - 1
    }
};
